description: The tribal politics continue as STORYTELLER continues her yarn. Vincent gets stronger.  Jack braces for more adventures as he struggles to make his way to Vincent…whom he is not sure is even alive.  KONG comes out from under the shadow of his parents, only to be held captive as a result of the power struggle within the tribe.  The legend of KONG: KING OF SKULL ISLAND is heating up during the 75th anniversary year for KONG, a worldwide icon!

Jack Driscoll continues to use the map of Skull Island in an effort to make his way through the tunnels to Vincent Denham, the son of Carl Denham…who is recovering after the incident at sea.  The Storyteller begins to explain the strange history of Skull Island and how KONG fits in to the mix.  This prequel/sequel to the Miriam C Cooper novel is based on the book by Joe DeVito.  Come celebrate KING KONG’s 75th anniversary!

DYNAMITE'S Red Sonja continues to impress fans and critics alike issue after issue! Now, the second hardcover collection is ready for your bookshelf as Michael Avon Oeming, Mel Rubi, Pablo Marcos, Lee Moder, and Stephen Sadowski unleash the Arrowsmiths!

* Limited Hardcover Printing - excellent companion to the sold out first hardcover collection!

* WRAP-AROUND COVER BY MEL RUBI!

* Reprinting Issues 8-12 Of The Fan-Favorite Red Sonja Series!

* Featuring the return of Kulan Gath

* Also include a complete gallery
name: Volume II: Arrowsmith

volume.name: Red Sonja: She-Devil with a Sword

description:
Know also, O Prince, that in the selfsame days that the Cimmerian did stalk the Hyborian Kingdoms, one of the few swords worthy to cross with his was that of a warrior-woman out of majestic Hyrkania. She, the mother of vengeance, hunter of evil, all fear for your souls... fear the RED SONJA!

-The Nemedian Chronicles

Writers Michael Avon Oeming and Mike Carey along with artist Mel Rubi have recreated Sonja for a whole new generation and this is where it all begins! This Dynamite Trade Paperback Collection of the all-new Red Sonja series features:

* Issues 1-6 and the grand finale of the opening arc, issue #0.

* Cover Gallery: Alex Ross, John Cassaday, Mike Turner, Marc Silvestri, Greg Land, and more!

* Two Covers: Ross and Turner (50/50 SPLIT)

* Director's Commentary with the creators

* A look at Mel Rubi's original Sonja designs

volume.name: Red Sonja: She-Devil with a Sword

description:
The superstar team of Warren Ellis and Kaare Andrews (SPIDER-MAN: REIGN) take the X-Men into the Heroic Age! Something's happening in the tiny East African city of Mbangwi. Something that requires immediate investigation. A newborn sprouts metal electrodes and explodes, taking out an entire hospital. Is this the first wave of mutant rebirth that the X-Men have been praying for - or something very, very different? Something sinister?

Collecting ASTONISHING X-MEN: XENOGENESIS #1-5 and material from ASTONISHING X-MEN: XENOGENESIS #1 DIRECTOR'S CUT.
name: Astonishing X-Men: Xenogenesis

description:
The X-Men's secrets revealed! Experience the origin of the X-Men's leader as you follow Cyclops from his childhood through his joining of the X-Men. Relive Nightcrawler's early days as a trapeze artist in Germany, the first time he teleported and the events that made him the hero he is today! See the small-town beginnings that helped forge Iceman, the coolest mutant of them all! Witness Emma Frost's rise from a mousy girl from a wealthy New England family to the rich and terrifying queen of a secret society to the leader of the X-Men! Plus: DEADPOOL: THE MAJOR MOTION PICTURE! You may have heard there's a Deadpool movie in the works. Wade Wilson's heard the same thing, and he's determined to tell his own story before Hollywood screws it up!

Collecting X-MEN ORIGINS: CYCLOPS, NIGHTCRAWLER, ICEMAN, EMMA FROST and DEADPOOL - plus bonus material from GIANT-SIZE X-MEN #1 and X-MEN #131.
name: HC/TPB

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: One day David Small awoke from a supposedly harmless operation to discover that he had been transformed into a virtual mute. A vocal cord removed, he had not been told that he had throat cancer and was expected to die. Readers will be riveted by his journey from speechless victim to his decision to flee his home at sixteen with nothing more than dreams of becoming an artist. Stitches will transform adolescent and adult readers alike with its deeply liberating vision.
name: Stitches

description:
The Super Hero Squad has its hands full safeguarding Super Hero City when the universe's great Collector sends his minions to hunt down every Squaddie for his collection; Fractals transform a tiny jellyfish into a giant slimy blob, put the 'Hulk' on everyone within its range and turn a paleontologist into a dinosaur in command of a dinosaur army; and the hypnotic Ringmaster mesmerizes the Squaddies to think they're circus performers, keeping them busy while Doctor Doom's Lethal Legion attempts to retrieve some Fractals from the S.H.I.E.L.D. Helicarrier! Plus: Thor reflects on his childhood, Captain America and the Falcon team up, Reptil plans a little April Fool's prank on the Squaddies, Doom dispatches Klaw to use his mastery of all sound and vibration to track down missing Fractals, the gang enjoys a day at the beach, and Abomination and M.O.D.O.K. pay a visit to the offices of Marble Comics!

Collecting SUPER HERO SQUAD #3-7.
name: Super Hero Squad: Super Hero Safari

volume.name: Super Hero Squad: Super Hero Safari

description:
Overview

HYDRA ZOMBIES! With a new and more powerful Resurrection Formula, Dr. Geist and Baron Strucker strike a blow at the very heart and soul of America. Cap-having been fired by the President and using the identify of 'The Captain', wages a secret war to stop Hydra before they can inflict the deepest of wounds on the American people. Jonathan Maberry welcomes Artist Kyle Hotz (Annihilation: Conquest) who brings his artistic magic to the mix as The Captain and an army of allies square off against a dreadful army of the dead!
name: Part 4

description: Is it a coincidence that humans have met Aliens in the cold reaches of space? Or is there something stitched into the very fabric of the cosmos that explains their inexorable spread through the galaxy? Deep-space rescue specialist Alecto Throop is about to find out that even a fight with the deadly creatures is nothing compared to meeting their masters . . . or the renegade human who has learned their secrets--ancient secrets.
name: TPB

description: Possessed by Rughal's fiendish weapon Blair Davis makes off with the Noor Stones belonging to members of The 99. Suddenly, the 99 Steps Foundation is under attack, Hammerfist, The Savage, The Sphinx, The Pathologist and Dr. Nanno are under Rughal's orders to capture the Noor Stones. Without their gems can the members of The 99 repel the attack or are they POWERLESS?
name: Powerless / Time and Time Again (part II)

description: The 99, issue #11! Is this the end of Raqib the watcher?
name: Watch the Watcher / Time and Time Again (part I)

description: Stalked and hunted by an unknown enemy, Raqib the Watcher warns Ramzi and The 99 about the mysterious figure know as Rughal. The 99 choose not hide within the safety of their headquarters but instead go to the aid of elephants being illegally hunted in Zimbabwe. While stalking poachers in the bush an unseen weapon attacks Jabbar, is this the work of Rughal?
name: The Blind Men and the Elephant(s) / The Light of Reason

description:
SWEET DREAMS, BABY...

On the ship Sulaco, its youngest passenger, Newt, lies safely in hypersleep. But in her head, the scenes of a grisly nightmare play over and over... a nightmare in which her family discovers a strange alien craft on the planet Acheron.

Based on James Cameron's screenplay, this gripping graphic novel tells the story of the ALIENS movie from the point of view of its young heroine.
name: Aliens: Newt's Tale

description: Locked in a deadly standoff, the police and The 99 face down a savage smuggler known as the Death Merchant. In the blink of an eye he takes a hostage and escapes further into the jungle. Hadya's tracking abilities can find him, Fattah can transport them there in an instant and Jabbar can provide the muscle but this triad isn't quite right for overcoming the Death Merchant's particular brand of evil.
name: Hate to Love / Opening Doors

description:
No Pain, No Gain

Doctor Ramzi, Jabbar and Noora examine a comatose young man in St. Louis, Missouri, and Noora detects the presence of very faint traces of Noor energy around his body. He is but the latest in a clinically unexplainable seizures that drew Ramzi's attention and proves his suspicions about the presence of a gem-bearer in St. Louis who is using his gift to hurt people. While they debate how to stop the aggressor, they are being spied on by Davis, a Canadian secret agent with a Noor stone of his own that grants him increased senses, as well as agents of Rughal.

After investigating other victims of the seizures and getting an anonymous tip that reveals that all the attacked individuals were responsible for vehicular homicides, Ramzi and his allies manage to identify John Weller, whose parents and sister were killed by the first victim in an episode of drunk driving. They go to Weller's residence and discover him to be a moody paraplegic who immediately attacks Ramzi, Noora and Jabbar with his pain powers, thinking that they intend to take away his Noor stone.

In the ensuing battle, doctor Ramzi and Rughal's spies are knocked out by Weller's painwave attacks and the house is destroyed by Jabbar, but Noora breaks the fight by forming a triad link that makes Weller realize that he had been abusing his powers for evil. Alerted by Davis of the impending arrival of police drawn by the disturbance, the 99 drive away and ask the american gembearer to join them as a new member of the 99. Weller, shamed by his previous actions, refuses until he can set things right and with the help of the other gembearers, sneaks into the hospital to take away the pain of his victims and heal them.

The Origin of Rughal (part I)

Rughal, whose body was torn apart by the Noor energy in his last experiment, is reborn in Titusville, Pennsylvania, in 1859 where he is found by oil field workers. Extremely confused, Rughal manages to communicate with Christopher, a Spanish speaking member of the work crew and learns that it has been nearly three centuries since his 'death' and that he has somehow been rejuvenated to an apparent age of thirty five.

As he talks with Christopher, Rughal learns that one of Christopher's ancestors was a sailor during Columbus' trips and sees a family heirloom that turns out to be a Noor stone, one of thirty three that were entrusted to Columbus to hide in the New World. Taking this as a sign, Rughal decides to find, gather again the ninety nine gemstones and claim their power for himself. To accomplish this ambitious goal, he decides to build a vast business empire.
name: No Pain, No Gain / The Origin of Rughal (part I)

description: Tony Montana is back-scraping the bottom of the barrel. The feds think they've got Tony under their thumb. A whole bunch of other scumbags believe they've got Miami under their control. And Tony's got nothin'-except for a gun, his ambition, and a plan to get back to the top. It ain't gonna be long until the bullet starts flying and the body count starts rising. Scarface's epic return continues.
name: The Scum Also Rises

description: Tony Montana is back, rising through the ranks, killing anybody stupid or suicidal enough to get in his way. Total control of the Miami drug trade is once again in sight, and the good life is just a few well-aimed bullets away. One big problem-the South American drug lord who thought he killed Tony just found out that Montana is very much alive. Tony needs this like he needs a hole in the head. Funny, the South American kingpin was thinking the exact same thing! The seedy, blood-soaked saga continues...
name: Everybody Angles

description:
Collects Our Army at War (1952-1977) #97-110. Written by Bob Kanigher. Art by Joe Kubert, Russ Heath and Irv Novick. Cover by Kubert.  
 
The legendary war hero is back in a second hardcover archive that collects stories originally published in 1960-1961! Witness the evolution of Sgt. Rock, as the stories take on a more mature, evolved tone.
name: Volume 2

description:
Collects Our Army at War (1952-1977) #111-125. Written by Robert Kanigher. Art by Joe Kubert, Russ Heath and Jerry Grandenetti. Cover by Joe Kubert.  
 
An intense portrait of combat and conflict featuring the World War II adventures of Sgt. Rock and his colorful band of fighting soldiers originally published in the early 1960s. Featuring an introduction by DCU editor Mark Chiarello.
name: Volume 3

description: A key piece of Green Lantern Corps history is collected for the first time in this new trade paperback presenting the 3-issue TALES OF THE GREEN LANTERN CORPS miniseries from 1981! Also included are backup Corps stories from GREEN LANTERN #148, 151-154, 161, 162 and 164-167.
name: Volume 1

volume.name: Tales of the Green Lantern Corps

description: It's another incredible collection of classic tales of the Corps from the pages of GREEN LANTERN #168, 169, 171-173, 177, 179-183, 185, 187-190 and TALES OF THE GREEN LANTERN CORPS ANNUAL #1, and featuring the work of Alan Moore, Dave Gibbons and many others!
name: Volume 2

volume.name: Tales of the Green Lantern Corps

description: For the first time, these classic tales of the Green Lantern Corps from GL #201-206 are collected, with the Corps in battle against Star Sapphire, establishing their Citadel headquarters and more!
name: Volume 3

volume.name: Tales of the Green Lantern Corps

description: X-Force has survived its first fights—but the stakes just keep getting higher, and the villains deadlier! A new Brotherhood of Evil Mutants, including Toad and Sauron, has formed and joined forces with the Morlocks, and their frightening attack on our heroes leaves one team member mortally wounded! Plus: the mysteries between Cable and Stryfe deepen, Deadpool goes after Domino and Cable, a government task force comes after X-Force, and one mutant is revealed to be an imposter! And just who are the X-Ternals? Collecting X-FORCE #5-15 and material from X-FORCE ANNUAL #1.
name: HC

description:
Story Titles

  • Rock Cristiano
  • Sancho De Sanchez
  • El Demonio Rojo
  • Por Un Punado De Sangre Capitulo 1
  • El Ojo Publico
  • Rosario Y Los Inagotables
  • Bitch. Bufo
  • Planeta Enfermo
  • Chistes Guarros
  • Pobres Pero Contentos
  • El Diario De Karol
  • Fanzines
  • Nunca Nada (Sangre De Barrio III) Capitulo 6
  • Kiosco, El Cuarto Poder
  • Cristobal Nazareto
  • El Porno Y El Mundo Real
  • Surcos Y Gemidos
  • Mecanismo Blanco

The greatest threat to the peace and stability of the galaxy in centuries has ended thanks to the legion of super-heroes. Now, the United Planets must reaffirm control over a devastated population, and the ideal situation is to make the legion an officially sanctioned peace-keeping force. Still financially and emotionally reeling from the tragic aftermath of the bring of war, will the 41st-century's band of rebellious teens be willing to work for the establishment?

The Legion also gains a powerful new ally as legendary 21st century hero Supergirl makes her debut in the new millennium.

The 21st Century's Girl of Steel wakes up 1,001 years later, convinced the whole reality is something she just dreamed up. And maybe it is.
name: Volume 3

volume.name: Supergirl And The Legion Of Super-Heroes: Strange Visitor From Another Century

description: THE 99 want to leave town for the holidays, but Dr. Ramzi has other ideas. Groan! He wants them to talk and learn about personal sacrifice—but as usual, real life intrudes and the team has to rush out to a mission in Afghanistan. Will THE 99 save the village from the breaking dam that is about to flood the town? And why is Noora being so distant?
name: Sacrifice

description: Enjoy this special 52 page one-shot issue of The 99: Storm Front!
name: Stormfront

description: Sent searching for Sami-- Hadya, Noora and Fattah find him at a retreat hidden high in the Himalayas, but he's not the only gem-bearer they find there.
name: Different Paths: Part One

description: The ancient city of Bam is burning and Buran's nephew is missing. Meanwhile in Paris, The 99's newest member Sami the Listener is also missing. Dr. Ramzi sends out two teams to locate the missing teens. The team that is sent to Bam discovers a new gem-bearer with a fiery ability, the other team discovers...
name: Firefight

description: Giant Robot wreaking havoc on the streets of Paris, whom do you call? The 99. But what do you do if Jami the Assembler created the robot? When Jami creates F.R.A.N.K.I.E. to protect the 99 Steps Foundation the robot's logic board acts a little too logically sending it on a misguided mission to render inactive all the gem-bearers in proximity.
name: There's something about F.R.A.N.K.I.E.

description: Noora the Light's father has been kidnapped and is being held for ransom, but it's not money the kidnapper wants, it's Noora and the power of her Noor Stone. Special: Manga back-up feature.
name: Turnabout / The 99 Manga

description: Chaos and confusion reign at the 99 Steps Foundation as the media breaks the news of The 99 member's true identities. Meanwhile, new gem-bearers are almost literally popping out of the woodwork.
name: Friends, Enemies and Network Interfaces

description: A team of 99 members is off to Cambodia to assist in a village's de-mining operation. On their mission they find that while their masks protect their identities, the masks place a barrier between them and the people they are trying to protect.
name: Masks

description: Jabbar the Powerful's little sister wants in on the superhero adventure and forms her own superhero team with the youngest and newest members of The 99. There's a gem-bearer in trouble beneath the streets of Paris - but what can a couple of kids do? Find out as we introduce: the Junior 99!
name: The Junior 99

description: The 99 take the fight to Rughal within his Hong Kong fortress. Untested in battle and outnumbered by his Drone Warriors, can the power of the 99's triads defeat Rughal's forces?
name: True Light & False (part III)

description: Dr. Ramzi wants the world to know about the fantastic new super heroes called The 99, however, their parents don't. Caught between their well intentioned parents and the desire to put their newly acquired powers to use the teens think they have a solution that will protect their families and their identities but will their plan of HIDING IN PLAIN SIGHT work?
name: True Light & False (part II)

description: The power of the Noor Stones, Rughal wants it but even he can't define it or truly understand how they work. And, despite the efforts of Dr Nanno and The Pathologist to harness Noor Stone energy, they remain empty-handed. That's when they call in the world's leading scientific expert of Noor Stone analysis Jami the Assembler, kidnapped from the 99 Steps Foundation and put to work for Rughal.
name: True Light & False (part I)

description:
Thor is dead! Asgard has been destroyed! Its gods are scattered across the Earth, living mortal lives with no memory of their past selves!

Can Sif, Balder, Ulik the Troll, the Warriors Three, the Enchantress and the other Lost Gods discover the truth about themselves in time to stop the world-destroying plot of Seth, God of Death? Featuring the Wrecking Crew, Spider-Man and an all-new Loki!

Collecting JOURNEY INTO MYSTERY #503-513.
name: TPB

description: Things are really rockin' in Seville, where the 99 Steps Foundation is throwing a party to get to know their new neighbors. The problem is, it isn't just the band that's doing the rockin' but Tremor, a villain with some earth shaking abilities. Oh, and there's an 800 pound gorilla in the room too.
name: Tremor Vs. The Singing Gorilla: A Prologue

description: Deep beneath the Artic Circle a researcher is trapped in a small submarine and running out of air. It's cold, dark and extremely dangerous with an underwater volcano that is about to blow as Dr. Ramzi sends two triad teams beneath the surface. Introducing the newest member of The 99, Mukit the Nourisher.
name: Boiling Cold

description: The 99 are on the move, they have outgrown their Paris headquarters and Dr. Ramzi decides to relocate the foundation to Spain. But like all moves, not everything goes as planned and there's a dramatic rescue along the way. Dr. Ramzi also learns that an ancient book about the Noor Stones he's been studying has a more sinister origin than he imagined.
name: What Is Written

description: Blackwolf and The Sphinx attack The 99, and the hidden retreats' own gem-bearers when they are most vulnerable, peacefully performing a Noor Stone exercise. Can the two groups work together to overcome Blackwolf and forge a lasting bond?
name: Different Paths: Part Three

description: Guided to the retreat by his students, Dr. Ramzi meets his counterpart in Madame Deneuve, a former gem-bearer who has developed the retreat as a haven for gem-bearers and others with special abilities. Here, like Ramzi's foundation the gem-bearers are encouraged to develop their gifts in peaceful surroundings. But something sinister is lurking and evil is revealed as Blackwolf and the Sphinx rear their ugly heads.
name: Different Paths: Part Two

description: If only Dr. Ramzi could see the future, then he'd know if he's doing the right thing by sending THE 99 into battle! He soul-searches after Hadya the Guide is seriously hurt on a mission-gone-wrong. As Hadya battles for her life, Dr. Ramzi calls in Aleem the All-Knowing, who uses his Noor Stone to see possible futures for THE 99.
name: Futures

description:
Batman Vs. Robin - Part 1: The Haunting of Wayne Manor

Could Bruce Wayne really be alive after all this time? Does a secret passage in stately Wayne Manor hold the clues to his fate?

Batman: Life After Death - Part 5: Mind Games

Batman's mind is not his own! What did the Dark Knight do while under the influence of one of his enemies?

Batwoman in Detective Comics - Cutter Part 2 of 3

Kathy Kane cuts into the heart of Gotham to uncover Bruce Wayne's most shocking and deadly cases!
name: The RETURN of BRUCE WAYNE Begins HERE!

description:
It's the Merc with a Mouth in a pulp caper filled with lies, spies and shapely thighs - courtesy of Mike Benson and Adam Glass (DEADPOOL: SUICIDE KINGS, LUKE CAGE NOIR) and Laurence Campbell (PUNISHER)! Wade Wilson. Codename: Deadpool. He's the CIA's deadliest agent. He's also certifiably insane, suffering from Multiple Personality Disorder and haunted by the ghosts of his past. In other words, he's the perfect soldier in a Cold War where it's impossible to tell friend from foe and reality from a lie.

Wilson is also the only one capable of hunting down a rogue CIA agent and recovering the stolen nuclear suitcase she's carrying before she hands it over to America's enemies. But who is this femme fatale, and why has she turned traitor? And is Deadpool crazy enough to survive, or will he become trapped in a web of international intrigue?

Collecting DEADPOOL PULP #1-4.
name: Deadpool Pulp

description:
Batman Vs. Robin - Part 2: Boneyard

It's a showdown at Wayne Manor, but has Bruce Wayne finally returned?

Batman: Life After Death - Part 6: Liberator

The Black Mask is revealed as Dick Grayson strikes at Gotham's criminal underworld.

Batwoman in Detective Comics - Cutter Part 3 of 3

Batwoman finally faces the Cutter - but are her wits sharp enough to defeat his deadly blades?
name: Black Mask REVEALED!

description:
Captain America and the Falcon continue their partnership against some of their greatest foes (the Red Skull, Arnim Zola the Bio-Fanatic and the Corporation) and some of their most bizarre (the Swine, Doughboy and the Vamp/Animus)!

Featuring guest appearances by the Hulk, Nick Fury and Sharon Carter! Plus: the debuts of the Constrictor and the Super-Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.! And the origin of Steve Rogers!

Collecting CAPTAIN AMERICA #206-230 and ANNUAL #4, and INCREDIBLE HULK #232.
name: Volume Six

description:
The Hood’s army strikes! The Secret Avengers are lured into a deadly trap by the sinister Dr Jonas Harrow – and the Dark Avengers are about to follow them! Both Avengers teams face total destruction in an action-packed adventure!

Includes material reprinted from New Avengers #55-57.
name: FALL of the AVENGERS!

description:
Norman Osborn and the Dark Avengers have the Secret Avengers cornered – and Luke Cage falls into their clutches! Has time finally run out for our heroes? Guest-starring Daredevil, the Thing and Doctor Voodoo!

Includes material reprinted from New Avengers #58-60.
name: NO WAY OUT!

description:
A Dark Avengers special! Ares discovers the secret his son has been keeping from him as he confronts Nick Fury!

Also: The Dark Avengers face a creature that can reshape reality, and the madness of Norman Osborn is exposed!

Includes material reprinted from Dark Avengers #9-11.
name: The MIND of NORMAN OSBORN!

description:
If only a few super heroes survived the ULTIMATUM - who's left to become the next super-powered team to be reckoned with? The NEW Ultimates!

With Thor gone, Loki takes his revenge - unleashing the worst of Asgard on Earth. Iron Man must gather the heroes for their biggest Ultimates adventure yet. But who's made the final cut? And who can't be trusted? The Ultimates face evil once again, and you'll never guess the new enemies they'll find - or should we say old friends?

Superstar creators Jeph Loeb and Frank Cho (in his Ultimate Comics debut!) bring you the new face of the Ultimate line!

Collecting ULTIMATE COMICS NEW ULTIMATES #1-5.
name: Ultimate Comics New Ultimates: Thor Reborn

volume.name: Ultimate Comics New Ultimates: Thor Reborn

name: Pericolo Giallo (6 / II)

description: Lost in the past, do Jabbar, Mumita, and Samda have what it takes to defeat the greatest monsters that ever lived—DINOSAURS! Meanwhile, Jami, Fattah, and Hadya are gem-less and alone in the frozen Ice Age. Can THE 99 reach across the centuries to bring the whole team home?
name: Timelost

description: Near the beginning of the Fantastic Four’s history, they fought with the Silver Surfer against a menace called Tyros the Terrible. As these sorts of super-powered struggles go, this was nothing terribly extraordinary: Tyros was eventually laid low and justice triumphed. Of course, there was a great deal of property damage involved, including the destruction of the top floors of a high rise building when Tyros threw the Silver Surfer through it. Still, the struggle was really nothing exceptional… unless you happened to live in that high rise.
name: Tales of the Marvels: Blockbuster

description: As Obo-san prepares to take a fateful step from which there can be no turning back, the evil emperor of Shinacea again mounts an effort to obtain the all-powerful Weapon of Heaven. And this time his tool will be Obo-san's deceased brother, Todosi!
